4.41	Korean_armed_resistance_in_the_Los_Angeles_riots	1992 Los Angeles riots	The 1992 Los Angeles Riots or South Central Riots, also known as the 1992 Los Angeles Civil Unrest were sparked on April 29, 1992, when a jury acquitted three white and one Hispanic Los Angeles Police Department officers accused in the videotaped beating of black motorist Rodney King following a high-speed pursuit. Thousands of people in the Los Angeles area rioted over the six days following the verdict.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8c/South_Central_Los_Angeles_1.jpg/200px-South_Central_Los_Angeles_1.jpg
